In recent decades, Alzheimers disease (AD) has garnered significant attention due to its rapid global prevalence. The cholinergic hypothesis posits that the degradation of acetylcholine by acetylcholinesterase (AChE) contributes to AD development. Despite existing anti-AChE drugs, their adverse side effects necessitate new agents. This study analyzed 150 bioactive phytochemicals from  Trachyspermum ammi

